# OS
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db

# Editors
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*.swo
*~

# Go
*.test
*.out
/bin/
/dist/

# Node / TypeScript
node_modules/
*.tsbuildinfo

# mdbook build output (the rendered site; src/ is canon)
/docs/book/book/

# Embedded-bus store: JetStream data + operator/account/user key material
# (default `sextant up --store` location). Never commit keys.
/.sextant/

# Ephemeral plane (ADR-0002): the agent workspace — specs, work-plans,
# breakdowns. Never committed; committed ⇔ signed-off.
/.work/

# Agent skills: the engineering skill bodies are COMMITTED under .claude/skills/
# so a fresh clone has them with no install step. Ignore everything else under
# .claude/, the other agents' skill copies, and the superpowers cache.
/.claude/*
!/.claude/skills/
/.agents/
/.superpowers/

# stray build output of `go build [-o <name>] ./clients/<app>` from the
# repo root (the apps moved out of ./cmd/ in the monorepo refactor)
/sextant
/sextant-*
/assistant
/coordinator
/dispatcher

# Generated dash embed artifact (ADR-0049): clients/sextant-dash/dashapi/web/app
# is assembled WHOLLY by scripts/build-dash-ui.sh (make ui / go:generate / CI /
# release) from the web-dash SPA source — transpiled *.js, copied static assets,
# the bundled vendor/sextant-bus.js, and the build.json stamp — then consumed by
# the go:embed in debug.go. Nothing here is committed; the committed SPA source
# (JSX, index.html, styles.css, favicon.png, image-slot.js, vendor/*.min.js, and
# the bundle/ scope) lives under clients/web-dash.
/clients/sextant-dash/dashapi/web/app/
